hods on JDK 13+. Install BlockHound only once per test JVM; use isolated test structure to avoid repeated-install side effects. If not relying on framework scheduler threads, explicitly configure a nonBlockingThreadPredicate before triggering a known blocking call such as Thread.sleep.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"BlockHound 1.0.8.RELEASE shades Byte Buddy 1.14.4, which officially supports Java class-file versions up to Java 21; newer JDKs may require additional experimental Byte Buddy settings or may fail.\",\n    \"Native Image verification may expose limitations because BlockHound depends on java.lang.instrument-style runtime instrumentation; local Gradle and Native Image runs remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0048aee1a904119d016a29178ea9908194a5827ae8d1dacb3a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 717, "output": 1249, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30638, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781077881027, "responseId": "resp_0048aee1a904119d016a29177978f08194a35adb6e00ea67a4"}}
